<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1258,1732]" box="[197,1319,1407,1434]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,1407,1433]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks:</emphasis>
Detailed descriptions of this species are given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Leloup, E." box="[908,1076,1408,1434]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref22382" refString="Leloup, E. (1940) Les Chitons du genre Cryptoplax Blainville, 1818. Bulletin du Musee royal d'Histoire naturelle de Belgique, 16 (33), 1 - 32, pls 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1940">Leloup (1940)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, A. J." box="[1134,1315,1408,1434]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="249 - 297" refId="ref21388" refString="Ferreira, A. J. (1983) Researches on the coast of Somalia. The chiton fauna (Mollusca Polyplacophora). Monitore Zoologico italiano, 9, 249 - 297." type="journal article" year="1983">Ferreira (1983)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1258,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
We attribute our valves to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[507,716,1445,1470]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Cryptoplacidae" genus="Cryptoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sykesi">
<emphasis box="[507,716,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cryptoplax sykesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the smooth jugal area and the sculpture of the lateropleural area, with 5–6 longitudinal riblets, some broken up in granules near the apex (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1367,1482,1508]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="26.[151,256,1778,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,903,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-408@26.[151,1436,903,1756]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 11A–L, Cryptoplax burrowi (E.A. Smith, 1884), Maldive. A–B, head valve, MLD02A. A, dorsal view. B, detail of the sculpture. C–E, intermediate valve, M65. C, dorsal view. D, detail of the sculpture. E, lateral view. F–H, tail valve, M65. F, dorsal view. G, lateral view. H, detail of the sculpture. I–L, living specimen, M07, girdle elements in situ. I, marginal spicules. J, ventral spicules. K–L, dorsal scales. M–O, Cryptoplax sykesi Thiele, 1909, intermediate valve, Maldive, M13. M, dorsal view. N, lateral view. O, detail of the sculpture. Scale bars 1 mm: C, E–G, N; 500 µm: A, M; 100 µm: B, D, H, I, K, L, O; 50 µm: J." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5330686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5330686/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 11O</figureCitation>
). Our material match with the valves found in 
<collectingCountry box="[630,772,1520,1546]" name="Madagascar" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(compare pl. 6, 
<figureCitation box="[967,1054,1520,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,255,1564,1588]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-222@29.[152,1435,194,1542]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14A–C, NHM labels, with informations on type material. A, Chiton laqueatus Sowerby, 1842, 5 specimens (lectotype and 4 paralectotypes), NHM 1988071/1-5. B–C, Cryptoplax burrowi E.A. Smith 1884. B, NHM 1992 053, syntypes, 4 specimens, H. Cuming colln., Port Adelaide, S. Australia. C, NHM 1881.11.1.100, syntype, detached valves, coll. Coppinger, Port Molle, Queensland. D, NHM label of Callochiton platessa Gould, 1846, S. Nilandu Atoll, Maldive, NHM 1903.4.11.71, living specimen collected by J.S. Gardiner (considered as Callochiton sp. in this work)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5330698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5330698/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Figs 
<quantity box="[1025,1054,1520,1546]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.683" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="3.556" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="in" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14</quantity>
</figureCitation>
–15 in Dell’Angelo 
<emphasis box="[1292,1345,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. 2004), only the 
<collectingCountry box="[253,350,1557,1583]" name="Maldives" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Maldive</collectingCountry>
intermediate valves seem more elevated than the 
<collectingCountry box="[935,1077,1557,1583]" name="Madagascar" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1258,1732]" box="[197,934,1594,1620]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
This is the first report of this species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[739,931,1594,1620]" name="Maldives" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Maldive Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1258,1732]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,360,1631,1657]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Distribution:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[369,580,1632,1657]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Cryptoplacidae" genus="Cryptoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sykesi">
<emphasis box="[369,580,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cryptoplax sykesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an intertidal to shallow sublittoral species, widespread in the western Indian Ocean. It is known from the Red Sea, 
<collectingCountry box="[713,816,1669,1695]" name="Somalia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[830,943,1669,1695]" name="Tanzania" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1120,1669,1695]" name="Mozambique" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, Natal, Amirante Islands, Geyser Bank (North of 
<collectingCountry box="[428,583,1706,1732]" name="Mozambique" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
Channel), 
<collectingCountry box="[712,853,1706,1732]" name="Madagascar" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[953,1145,1706,1732]" name="Maldives" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Maldive Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
